article.description: Liz Shimek scored 25 points  and grabbed 15 rebounds to lift No. 11 Michigan State to a 62-56 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi.
article.headline: Islanders' five-game winning streak ends
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Michigan (Ticker) -- Liz Shimek scored 25 points  and grabbed 15 rebounds to lift No. 11 Michigan State to a 62-56 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi.

Behind Shimek's strong play, the Spartans outscored the Islanders 44-22 in the paint and won the battle of the boards, 52-39.

Neither team shot very well from the field, each hitting 36 percent. The Spartans made 12-of-18 free throws, compared to 1-of-3 for the Islanders, while Texas A&M-CC was 9-of-22 from beyond the arc and Michigan State 0-for-7.

Kristin Haynie scored 14 points and Kelli Roehrig added 13 for Michigan State (9-1).

Lindsey Van Dorn scored 16 points to lead the Islanders (8-2), who lost for the first time on the road this season and had a five-game wining streak snapped.
